In the framework of this course, the concepts of community and anchor institutions, and ethical and practical issues of community development will be discussed. The various organisations working with the communities and their main activities will be introduced from the perspective of community development.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide students with knowledge about the concepts of community and anchor institutions, ethical and practical issues of community development, including the community developer's self-care, to introduce the various organisations working with the communities.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of this course, the student: *	knows concepts related to communities and anchor institution, and is aware of the meaning of these concepts *	is able to analyse ethical issues related to community development and plan community-oriented activities by being aware of these issues *	is able to analyse the community heterogeneity, and consider it when planning activities for the community *	knows various organisations working with the community *	knows and is able to plan joint activities with the community *	is familiarized with practical suggestions related to community development and support  *	knows the basics of community developer's self-care.
